This documentation describes App Automator for PCF, including information about installing and configuring App Automator. It also describes how developers can define App Automator triggers and actions to execute automated actions against apps in their PCF deployment.

## About App Automator for PCF

App Automator for PCF executes automated actions against apps based on triggers. For example, App Automator can automatically scale an app up or down when app metrics such as memory or CPU reach a given threshold. Developers define these actions and triggers in an App Automator manifest file. 

Operators can install App Automator for PCF on one or more spaces in a PCF deployment. For more information about installing and configuring App Automator for PCF, see [Using App Automator for PCF](../using.html).